*stats_dens_pmf_negative_binomial*

(PECL stats >= 1.0.0)

stats_dens_pmf_negative_binomial â€” Probability mass function of the negative
binomial distribution

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  stats_dens_pmf_negative_binomial(float $x, float $n, float $pi): float~

Returns the probability mass at {x}, where the random variable follows the
negative binomial distribution of which the number of the success is {n} and
the success rate is {pi}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{x}

  The value at which the probability mass is calculated

{n}

  The number of the success of the distribution

{pi}

  The success rate of the distribution

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The probability mass at {x} or false for failure.


